ourage afterwards.\n\n- Anonymous\n|\nI have caressed a small child’s hair, and in doing so, know there is a God.\n\n- Lewis\n|\nFEAR is always about the FUTURE, felt in the PRESENT based on the PAST!\n\n- Harrish\n|\nAs long as you're not hurting anyone or anything, including your future self, do only that which makes you happy.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nThe bright side of the planet moves toward darknessAnd the cities are falling asleep, each in its hour,And for me, now as then, it is too much.There is too much world.\n\n- Czesław Miłosz, The Separate Notebooks\n|\nIt is essential that you follow your own idea of passion, even if to others it looks like suffering.\n\n- Bryant McGill, Simple Reminders: Inspiration for Living Your Best Life\n|\nFathers, your are the head and strength of the family unit. If you are not in place, there is a weakness in the link.\n\n- Anita\n|\nI disagree with a lot of those changes, however at the end of the day - I go down to recruit graduation at least once or twice a year.\n\n- R.\n|\nThere's a very thin line between rightfully protesting, and protesting so much that it becomes clear you're trying to hide something.\n\n- Aimee Carter, Queen\n|\nIf I only looked at what I've lost, I'd never be able to see what I have.\n\n- Cindy\n|\nYou possess other people's...bodies.'He accepted that statement with a nod.'Do you want to possess my body?''I want to do a lot of things to your body, but that's not one of them.\n\n- Becca Fitzpatrick, Hush, Hush\n|\nCould be. I’m a pretty dangerous dude when I’m cornered.”“Yeah,” said the voice from under the table, “you go to pieces so fast people get hit by the shrapnel.\n\n- Douglas Adams, The Restaurant at the End of the Universe\n|\nAs a rule, the human mind gets attached to possessions very firmly. They don’t want to lose anything. They hold on to the little possession and can’t see the big possibilities.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIt's three words 'Alter your life' which mean change your life. It's not so easy, but it's not so hard everyone can do it.\n\n- Deyth\n|\nIntoxicatedWith the madnessI'm in love withMy sadnessBullshit beggars, enchanted kingdomFashion victims through their charcoaled teeth\n\n- Billy\n|\nYou possess great strength, great spirit and great soul.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nPunctuation, is? fun!\n\n- Daniel Keyes, Flowers for Algernon\n|\nFrom the same window, you keep seeing the same view!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nBut Perfection never appealed to me.It's the beauty and honesty behind imperfections, that I fall in love with.\n\n- Wordions\n|\nI ran the wrong kind of business, but I did it with integrity.\n\n- Sydney\n|\nWhen you see yourself in a shattered mirror, don't think of it as the broken pieces of yourself. Think of it as all of the pieces that make up you.\n\n- Blaque\n|\nIt's a funny thing, the less people have to live for, the less nerve they have to risk losing nothing.\n\n- Zora\n|\nI don’t want to take away anybody’s religion, but simply to make them see what religion really means.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Illusion of Religion: A Treatise on Religious Fundamentalism\n|\nReason and logic, fused with intuition and empathy, equals awakened consciousness and spirituality.\n\n- Dara\n|\nIf a man treats life artistically, his brain is his heart.\n\n- Oscar Wilde, The Picture of Dorian Gray\n|\nIt was not my intention to collapse; no, I would die standing.\n\n- Knut Hamsun, Hunger\n|\nTo find out how much we can do or how far we can go, we have to challenge ourselves constantly.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI know he's rich. He knows he's rich, too.\n\n- Lorraine Hansberry, A Raisin in the Sun\n|\nI felt as if something hung there in the back of my mind, waiting to tarnish whatever happiness I might find. Is it safer to be unhappy? Nothing ever wants to take that away.\n\n- Storm Constantine, The Enchantments of Flesh and Spirit\n|\nI would dream of a place, a place to shelter all my madness.\n\n- J. Limbu, Anemone: The Windflower\n|\nT